[{"text": "Marco Tempest: What I'd like to show you today", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is something in the way of an experiment.", "start": 17.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Today's its debut.", "start": 20.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a demonstration of augmented reality.", "start": 22.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the visuals you're about to see are not prerecorded.", "start": 25.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They are live", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and reacting to me in real time.", "start": 30.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I like to think of it as a kind of technological magic.", "start": 32.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "So fingers crossed.", "start": 37.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And keep your eyes on the big screen.", "start": 40.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Augmented reality", "start": 44.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the melding of the real world", "start": 46.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with computer-generated imagery.", "start": 49.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It seems the perfect medium", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to investigate magic", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and ask, why, in a technological age,", "start": 56.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we continue to have", "start": 59.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this magical sense of wonder.", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Magic is deception,", "start": 64.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but it is a deception we enjoy.", "start": 67.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "To enjoy being deceived,", "start": 70.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an audience must first", "start": 72.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "suspend its disbelief.", "start": 74.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was the poet Samuel Taylor Coleridge", "start": 76.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who first suggested this receptive state of mind.", "start": 79.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Samuel Taylor Coleridge: I try to convey a semblance of truth in my writing", "start": 82.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to produce for these shadows of the imagination", "start": 86.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a willing suspension of disbelief", "start": 89.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that, for a moment,", "start": 92.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "constitutes poetic faith.", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MT: This faith in the fictional is essential", "start": 96.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for any kind of theatrical experience.", "start": 99.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Without it,", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a script is just words.", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Augmented reality", "start": 106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is just the latest technology.", "start": 108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And sleight of hand", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is just an artful demonstration", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of dexterity.", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We are all very good at suspending our disbelief.", "start": 116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We do it every day,", "start": 118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "while reading novels,", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "watching television", "start": 122.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or going to the movies.", "start": 124.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We willingly enter fictional worlds", "start": 126.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where we cheer our heroes", "start": 128.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and cry for friends we never had.", "start": 130.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Without this ability", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is no magic.", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was Jean Robert-Houdin,", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "France's greatest illusionist,", "start": 139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who first recognized the role of the magician", "start": 141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a storyteller.", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said something that I've posted on the wall of my studio.", "start": 145.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Jean Robert-Houdin: A conjurer is not a juggler.", "start": 148.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He is an actor playing the part of a magician.", "start": 150.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "MT: Which means magic is theater", "start": 154.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and every trick", "start": 156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a story.", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The tricks of magic", "start": 160.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "follow the archetypes of narrative fiction.", "start": 162.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are tales of creation and loss,", "start": 164.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "death and resurrection,", "start": 168.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and obstacles that must be overcome.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Now many of them are intensely dramatic.", "start": 175.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Magicians play with fire and steel,", "start": 178.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "defy the fury of the buzzsaw,", "start": 180.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "dare to catch a bullet", "start": 182.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or attempt a deadly escape.", "start": 184.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "But audiences don't come to see the magician die,", "start": 188.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they come to see him live.", "start": 191.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because the best stories", "start": 193.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "always have a happy ending.", "start": 195.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The tricks of magic have one special element.", "start": 197.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They are stories with a twist.", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now Edward de Bono argued", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that our brains are pattern matching machines.", "start": 205.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He said that magicians deliberately exploit", "start": 208.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the way their audiences think.", "start": 211.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Edward de Bono: Stage magic relies almost wholly", "start": 214.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on the momentum error.", "start": 216.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The audience is led to make assumptions or elaborations", "start": 218.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that are perfectly reasonable,", "start": 221.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but do not, in fact, match", "start": 223.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what is being done in front of them.", "start": 225.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MT: In that respect,", "start": 227.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "magic tricks are like jokes.", "start": 229.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Jokes lead us down a path", "start": 231.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to an expected destination.", "start": 234.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But when the scenario we have imagined suddenly flips", "start": 236.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into something entirely unexpected,", "start": 239.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we laugh.", "start": 241.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The same thing happens", "start": 243.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when people watch magic tricks.", "start": 245.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The finale", "start": 247.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "defies logic,", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "gives new insight into the problem,", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and audiences express their amazement", "start": 254.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with laughter.", "start": 257.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's fun to be fooled.", "start": 259.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "One of the key qualities of all stories", "start": 261.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that they're made to be shared.", "start": 263.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We feel compelled to tell them.", "start": 265.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "When I do a trick at a party --", "start": 267.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 270.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that person will immediately pull their friend over", "start": 272.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and ask me to do it again.", "start": 274.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They want to share the experience.", "start": 276.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That makes my job more difficult,", "start": 278.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because, if I want to surprise them,", "start": 280.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I need to tell a story that starts the same,", "start": 282.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but ends differently --", "start": 284.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a trick with a twist", "start": 286.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on a twist.", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It keeps me busy.", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now experts believe", "start": 292.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that stories go beyond our capacity for keeping us entertained.", "start": 294.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "We think in narrative structures.", "start": 298.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We connect events and emotions", "start": 300.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and instinctively transform them", "start": 304.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into a sequence that can be easily understood.", "start": 307.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a uniquely human achievement.", "start": 310.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We all want to share our stories,", "start": 312.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "whether it is the trick we saw at the party,", "start": 314.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the bad day at the office", "start": 317.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or the beautiful sunset we saw on vacation.", "start": 319.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Today, thanks to technology,", "start": 322.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we can share those stories as never before,", "start": 325.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by email, Facebook,", "start": 328.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "blogs, tweets,", "start": 331.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on TED.com.", "start": 333.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The tools of social networking,", "start": 335.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "these are the digital campfires", "start": 338.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "around which the audience gathers", "start": 340.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to hear our story.", "start": 342.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We turn facts into similes and metaphors,", "start": 344.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and even fantasies.", "start": 347.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We polish the rough edges of our lives", "start": 349.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so that they feel whole.", "start": 351.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Our stories make us the people we are", "start": 353.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and, sometimes, the people we want to be.", "start": 356.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They give us our identity", "start": 359.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and a sense of community.", "start": 361.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And if the story is a good one,", "start": 364.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it might even make us smile.", "start": 367.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 375.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 379.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 381.26, "duration": 4.0}]